Cell["\<\
The default split shape gives one diagram per diagrammatically prime factor, \
and the colors are meaningful across the summands: same color, same link \
component. The trefoil factor draws entirely in component 0's color -- the \
same color as the strand that threads the Hopf factor -- because that is the \
component the trefoil is tied into:\
\>", "ExampleText",ExpressionUUID->"d59b1d3a-ef30-4234-969b-76c4ed315a4d"],

